'''Real Medicine Foundation (RMF)''' is a US-based [[Nonprofit organization|nonprofit]] public charity that provides humanitarian support and development around the world, helping communities recover from natural disasters, conflict, and poverty. RMF was created in response to the [[2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami|2004 Indian Ocean tsunami]], which killed over 200,000 people and displaced thousands more.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.britannica.com/event/Indian-Ocean-tsunami-of-2004|title=Indian Ocean tsunami of 2004 {{!}} Facts & Death Toll|work=Encyclopedia Britannica|access-date=2018-09-18|language=en}}</ref> Pediatrician Dr. Martina Fuchs traveled to [[Sri Lanka]], where she opened a small medical clinic in the Mawella Camp for tsunami survivors. Based on the needs she witnessed and patients requiring longer-term support, Dr. Fuchs founded Real Medicine Foundation in 2005.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.voanews.com/a/a-13-2008-04-24-voa22-66815617/256214.html|title=Real Medicine Foundation, Born in Asian Tsunami, Helps in 11 Countries|work=VOA|access-date=2018-09-18|language=en}}</ref> As of September 2018, the organization has grown to include over seventy active projects and has worked in twenty-four countries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.realmedicinefoundation.org/|title=Real Medicine Foundation|website=www.realmedicinefoundation.org|access-date=2018-09-18}}</ref> [[File:RMF Logo.jpg|alt=Real Medicine Foundation|thumb|Real Medicine Foundation Logo]] Real Medicine Foundation defines holistic, or “real” medicine, as “providing medical/physical, emotional, economic, and social support.” Because of this philosophy, the organization’s projects often start with health clinics and disaster relief, but evolve into additional support that includes health research, mobile clinics and outreach, health systems strengthening, education and school support, vocational training, psychological trauma support, and [[malnutrition]] eradication.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.realmedicinefoundation.org/about-us/our-approach/|title=What We Do - Real Medicine Foundation|website=www.realmedicinefoundation.org|access-date=2018-09-18}}</ref> The end goal is “Liberating Human Potential”; by employing only nationals for in-country operations and working closely with communities in need, the organization works to empower local community members and leaders to create long-term solutions to [[Natural disaster|natural disasters]], conflict, and [[poverty]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Fuchs|first=Martina|date=Spring 2017|title=Liberating human potential|url=http://www.philanthropy-impact.org/sites/default/files/pdf/pi_magazine_15_final.pdf|journal=Philanthropy Impact Magazine|volume=|issue=15|pages=42-43|via=}}</ref> ----
